1323	\begin{theorem}[The quotient profile is necessary for MCA at large primes]\label{thm:qnecessity}
1324	Let $H_n\le\F_p^\times$ be smooth of order $n$, let $C=\RS[\F_p,H_n,\rho n]$, and let $\eta\in(0,1-\rho)$.  Assume the maximum defining $\mathcal Q_{H_n}(\eta)$ in \cref{def:qprofile} is nonempty, let $M^*$ be a divisor attaining it, and put $N^*=n/M^*$.  Suppose
1325	\[
1326	        p>(2(\rho N^*+1))^{N^*/2}.
1327	\]
1328	Then the exact quotient-floor lower bound is
1329	\[
1330	        \emca(C,1-\rho-\eta)
1331	        \ge
1332	        \frac{\Acl(N^*,\rho N^*+1)}{p}.
1333	\]
1334	If moreover $N^*\to\infty$ along the sequence, then
1335	\[
1336	        \Acl(N^*,\rho N^*+1)
1337	        =
1338	        2^{(\beta(\rho)/\HH(\rho))\mathcal Q_{H_n}(\eta)(1-o(1))}.
1339	\]
1340	Consequently, along sequences with $N^*\to\infty$, if $\emca(C,1-\rho-\eta)\le n^A/p$ at such a prime, then
1341	\[
1342	        \mathcal Q_{H_n}(\eta)
1343	        \le
1344	        \frac{\HH(\rho)}{\beta(\rho)}A\log_2n\,(1+o(1)).
1345	\]
1346	For bounded $N^*$ the exact bound stands while the profile is $O(1)$, so the consequence is vacuous there.  At the deployed rates $1/2,1/4,1/8,1/16$, the constants $\HH(\rho)/\beta(\rho)$ are approximately $1.262$, $1.082$, $1.024$, and $1.009$.
