1349	\begin{proof}
1350	A divisor qualifying for \cref{def:qprofile} satisfies $M^*>\eta n$, equivalently $1/N^*>
1351	\eta$.  The radius $1-\rho-1/N^*$ is therefore below $1-\rho-\eta$, and bad slopes at the former radius remain bad at the latter by monotonicity in \cref{def:mca}.  Applying \cref{prop:qfloor} at quotient order $N^*$ gives at least $\Acl(N^*,\rho N^*+1)$ bad slopes, which is the exact bound.  If $N^*\to\infty$, then
1352	\[
1353	        \mathcal Q_{H_n}(\eta)
1354	        =\log_2\binom{N^*-1}{\rho N^*}
1355	        =\HH(\rho)N^*(1-o(1)),
1356	        \qquad
1357	        \log_2\Acl(N^*,\rho N^*+1)=\beta(\rho)N^*(1-o(1)),
1358	\]
1359	by Stirling and \cref{thm:exactcount}, which gives the asymptotic identity and the displayed necessary condition.
1360	\end{proof}
