1375	\begin{remark}[Margin against the conjectured positive half]\label{rem:margin}
1376	\Cref{thm:qnecessity} gives the strongest value-counting attack available from the quotient rigidity theory.  If $\mathcal Q_{H_n}(\eta)\le B_Q\log_2 n$, the attack produces $n^{(\beta/\HH)B_Q(1-o(1))}$ bad slopes, while a target upper bound of the form $n^{B_Q}/p$ would still survive by the margin
1377	\[
1378	        \HH(\rho)-\beta(\rho)=
1379	        \begin{cases}
